"title": "5420: music",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5420",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Music played a major role in the lives of people in biblical times. It was used in both sacred and secular activities and was most often associated with joy and celebration.</p>\n<h2>Music comes from God</h2>\n<h3>God's presence inspires music</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:13\">PSA 96:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:4\">PSA 98:4</a></p>\n<h3>It is a gift of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:10\">JOB 35:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Music was closely associated with praise and worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:2\">PSA 33:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:3\">JDG 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:27\">NEH 12:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:6\">PSA 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:7\">PSA 57:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:1-Ps81:2\">PSA 81:1–81:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps87:7\">PSA 87:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:3\">PSA 92:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:2\">PSA 95:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:4\">PSA 98:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps108:1\">PSA 108:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:9\">PSA 144:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:7\">PSA 147:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:3\">PSA 149:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps150:1-Ps150:6\">PSA 150:1–150:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19-Eph5:20\">EPH 5:19–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Music was employed extensively in the tabernacle and the temple</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:6-1Chr25:7\">1CH 25:6–25:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:31-1Chr6:32\">1CH 6:31–6:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:12-2Chr5:14\">2CH 5:12–5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:15\">2CH 35:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:65\">EZR 2:65</a></p>\n<h2>Music and the psalms</h2>\n<h3>Many psalms are dedicated to the ``director of music''</h3>\n<p><strong>PSA 11:0</strong> <em>See also</em> PSA 13:0, PSA 31:0, PSA 42:0, PSA 49:0, PSA 77:0, PSA 139:0; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:19\">HAB 3:19</a></p>\n<h3>The titles of some psalms probably give an indication of melody</h3>\n<p><strong>PSA 9:0</strong> <em>See also</em> PSA 22:0, PSA 45:0, PSA 56:0, PSA 57:0, PSA 58:0, PSA 59:0, PSA 60:0, PSA 69:0, PSA 75:0, PSA 80:0</p>\n<h3>The titles of some psalms indicate specific musical accompaniment</h3>\n<p><strong>PSA 4:0</strong> <em>See also</em> PSA 5:0, PSA 6:0, PSA 54:0, PSA 55:0, PSA 61:0, PSA 67:0, PSA 76:0; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:19\">HAB 3:19</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of music</h2>\n<h3>To celebrate victory</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:27-2Chr20:28\">2CH 20:27–20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:21\">EXO 15:1–15:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:1-Judg5:31\">JDG 5:1–5:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:7\">1SA 18:6–18:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:32\">ISA 30:32</a></p>\n<h3>At times of celebration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:27\">GEN 31:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:12\">JOB 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa16:10\">ISA 16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:14\">LAM 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:13\">EZK 26:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:25\">LUK 15:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:22\">REV 18:22</a></p>\n<h2>At banquets</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:12\">ISA 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:4-Amos6:6\">AMO 6:4–6:6</a></p>\n<h3>As an expression of joy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:7\">1SA 18:6–18:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:5\">2SA 6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:40\">1KI 1:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job21:12\">JOB 21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:13\">JAS 5:13</a></p>\n<h3>For pleasure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:8\">ECC 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:35\">2SA 19:35</a></p>\n<h3>For divine inspiration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:14-2Kgs3:15\">2KI 3:14–3:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10\">1SA 18:10</a></p>\n<h3>To relieve depression</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:23\">1SA 16:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:16-1Sam16:18\">1SA 16:16–16:18</a></p>\n<h3>At times of mourning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:17-2Sam1:18\">2SA 1:17–1:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:23\">MAT 9:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:31\">JOB 30:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job35:10\">JOB 35:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:36\">JER 48:36</a></p>\n<h2>Prophets sometimes prophesied to musical accompaniment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:5-1Sam10:6\">1SA 10:5–10:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:14-2Kgs3:19\">2KI 3:14–3:19</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of music is a sign of judgment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:8\">ISA 24:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:22\">REV 18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Music in pagan worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:5\">DAN 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:7\">DAN 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:10\">DAN 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:15\">DAN 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Music played by prostitutes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:16\">ISA 23:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The misuse of music</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:12\">PSA 69:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:3\">PSA 137:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:4-Dan3:7\">DAN 3:4–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:23\">AMO 5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:5\">AMO 6:5</a></p>",
